Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Chloe Kim

2023-03-07

My meme

My motivation for creating this meme was to show how my uni life is going. When I first saw an image on the left, I thought this would be the way I look like every morning when attempting to get out of bed. Then I have searched for another lion image staring at something so that it would resemble the way I look when I am staring at my phone. 

library(magick)

# first image
lion_1 <- image_read("lion.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me every morning \n regretting about not sleeping before 12",
                            color = "#FFFFFF",
                            size = 30,
                            font = "Impact",
                            gravity = "south")


# second image
lion_2 <- image_read("lion_2.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(550) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me every night \n searching for something fun after 12",
                            color = "#000000",
                            size = 35,
                            font = "Impact",
                            gravity = "south")

# text
ml_text <- image_blank(width = 1050, 
                       height = 100, 
                       color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Uni Life",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

lion_vector <- c(lion_1, lion_2)

top_row <- image_append(ml_text)
bottom_row <- image_append(lion_vector)

meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

image_append(meme)

image_write(meme, "lion.png")

My animated GIF

My motivation was to create an animated GIF about something that I like. Since Minions have been one of my favourite characters since high school, I found an animated gif and screenshoted to create a new gif from an existing animated MINIONS GIF with a text emphasizing how cute they are! 

library(magick)

# images
frame1 <- image_read("1.png")
frame2 <- image_read("2.png")
frame3 <- image_blank(width = 700, 
                      height = 200, 
                      color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "MINIONS",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "north")
frame4 <- image_read("3.png")
frame5 <- image_read("4.png")

frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5)

# creating gif
my_gif <- image_animate(frames, fps = 0.5)

# saving gif as an image file
my_gif %>% 
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
